Cofina SGPS SA (CFN) , a Portuguese
newspaper publisher, advanced the most in more than seven years
in Lisbon trading on an announcement that it will join the
countryâ€™s benchmark stock index.  The  stock  climbed 8 euro cents, or 22 percent, to 44 cents,
the biggest jump since February 2005. The stock has dropped 42
percent this year, giving Cofina a market value of 45 million
euros ($56 million).  The NYSE Euronext Lisbon exchange announced the quarterly
review of the PSI-20 index after the close of trading yesterday.
The changes to index membership take effect on Sept. 24.  To contact the reporter on this story:
